  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2432",
  "title": "Using checkbox in hierarchical menu widget",
  "body": "Adding a checkbox in a hierarchical menu template for item has the following behavior when clicking on the box:\r\n - ok on the first level\r\n - on the second level, it goes back to the root instead of selecting the item\r\n - on the second level, it's ok if we click on the text\r\n\r\n[See it live here.\r\n](https://codepen.io/bobylito/pen/boorrR?editors=1000)\r\n\r\nI've been able to track the issue in the RefinementList which has a smart behavior to avoid double clicking but that was not built with checkbox in mind for hierarchical facet. https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/49f1f4bb68e371928d824e407bfca6f467405502/src/components/RefinementList/RefinementList.js#L98-L131",
